  "title": "Condominium Manager",
  "description": "<p>Our client is seeking an experienced Condominium Manager to oversee residential properties across multiple locations. </p><p><u>Key Responsibilities </u></p><ul><li>Oversee maintenance of common areas, facilities, and equipment, plan preventive maintenance and improve works. </li><li>Serve as the primary liaison for residents, on all inquiries, feedback and report on correspondence. </li><li>Uphold compliance with MCST by-laws, safety requirements, and all applicable statutory and regulatory standards.</li><li>Oversee financial administration and annual budget planning, maintaining strong fiscal discipline and a forward-looking approach to financial management.</li><li>Manage the overall day-to-day operations of the residential development, including supervision of maintenance activities and facilities management services.</li></ul><p><u>Requirements</u></p><ul><li>Diploma/Degree in Facilities/ Property Management, or related field.</li><li>At least 3 years of hand-on experience in managing residential property - 400 units and above.</li><li>Strong intercommunication skills with solution-oriented mindset, resourceful and independence.</li><li>Able to build good relationships at all levels.</li><li>Proficient in MS office and property management software.</li></ul><p><br />If you have a background in MCST or residential property management and are passionate about delivering excellent estate operations, we’d love to hear from you. </p><p>Click apply now.</p><p>EA: One Stop Placement Pte Ltd (Lic: 14C7105)</p><p>Rena Kuek (R25127922) Or email your resume to hr@osp.sg</p>",
